  "title": "amnoise",
  "description": "This MEG dataset contains neuroimaging data from a single infant subject collected to investigate auditory processing and language development in children at risk for dyslexia. The data were acquired during a linguistic sensitive period and are used to examine the relationship between early auditory deficits and subsequent language outcomes, with particular focus on theta oscillatory activity during native phoneme learning.",
  "methods_description": "MEG data were collected from an infant subject and converted to BIDS format using MNE-BIDS. The dataset includes magnetoencephalographic recordings acquired during auditory and linguistic tasks.",
